PURPOSE: The prevalence of osteoporosis has continuously increased over the past 
decades and it is set to increase substantially as life expectancy rises 
steadily. Fragility or osteoporotic fractures of the pelvis often occur after 
low energy falls e.g. from standing, however, some patients present with assumed 
insufficiency fractures of the pelvis without a previous trauma. Osteoporotic 
